snippet.textDisplay:
I mean I’m a huge fan overall but I’ve got a thing or two to say (btw this is all constructive criticism, not hate):

How is every three videos the scariest night of your lives? And I’ve been saying this for months: you have to stop overreacting. Not every little sound is a demon trying to possess you. You guys say you want answers, but when something happens everyone screams and runs away. You can’t want for answers, but shut them out every time there’s an opportunity to discover them.

You guys have been doing this for majority of your videos ever since Queen Mary. Everyone wants answers and says “we will do this and that” yet run away once things start to happen. Now don’t get me wrong, put your safety first. At the same time, stop being dramatic and running away from every little thing. I wouldn’t go as far to call you guys cowards, but sometimes you’re all doing too much. You have to be patient, calm, and take things slow. These types of things require patience and analyzing, but not assuming all the time.

Another note: please stop putting so many sound effects and editing over peers of the videos. It takes away from the genuinely and honesty of it all. We can’t hear anything when you say “listen” then add loud music to it all.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey sam and Colby did yall ever went to  Emily Morgan Hotel, San Antonio? Information below👇

Housed in a historic neo-Gothic building with a reputation for paranormal activity, the 177-room boutique Emily Morgan Hotel has a prime downtown location across from the Alamo. It also at one time was a medical facility, so the property housed a morgue and a psychiatric ward. Reports of unexplained noises, apparitions, and the feeling of being touched are pretty frequent. If you want to up your chances of a paranormal encounter, book a room on the seventh, ninth, eleventh, or twelfth floors. Also, as a nod to the hotel's notoriety for paranormal activity, the on-site Oro Restaurant and Bar offers a Psychic Happy Hour with palm readings on Thursday nights.
